<section sectnbr = "9K">
<servcat sctnbr = "09" scnbr = "11">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A9B06015" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Quarter-Pillar Outer Panel Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
The figure below shows condition where following parts are removed.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front fender 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9A06005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Fuel filler door panel 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9A06010"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0105.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "55.869mm" ver = "02" gw = "228" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06015001">
<title>
Precautions
</title>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Welding method and number of welding points are the same on both sides. This repair instruction shows procedure for left side.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The dimensions shown in the figure are reference values when cutting replacement part placed on top of existing part. Determine most appropriate cutting (or joint) line considering both size of replacement part and condition of existing part.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06015002">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Mark at the shown position and cut quarter-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not damage parts underneath roof panel or side sill outer panel when cutting.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drill out welding spots.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend open metal tab (arrow) and remove quarter-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B9B0001.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "234.089mm" ver = "01" gw = "494" gh = "647"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.472in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "6.364in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
When heating around sealer application portion to detach body sealer, be sure that temperature of said portion does not reach 170 &#176;C (338 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
This symbol indicates that quarter-pillar outer panel and rear wheel house outer panel are replaced at the same time.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Vehicle left side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Vehicle right side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A9B06015003">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before conducting any weld, check installation position and condition for installation part(s). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 / 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 / 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Proceed repair while taking into consideration installation of parts that affect appearance. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A9B04003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Apply body sealer to fuel filler box.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Install fuel filler box.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "1">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A9B0096.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "104.943mm" ver = "02" gw = "188" gh = "281"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.558in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Applied part of body sealer.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new quarter-pillar outer panel to vehicle body and cut in stacked condition.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove quarter-pillar outer panel and apply body sealer.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Reinstall quarter-pillar outer panel to vehicle body.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld or plug weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Conduct continuous weld.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply anticorrosion wax to back side of continuous weld part.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Bend in metal tab (arrow) of quarter-pillar outer panel.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B9B0002.jpg" width = "183.000mm" height = "234.588mm" ver = "01" gw = "494" gh = "648"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.472in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "5.378in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Conduct resistance spot weld as three panel thickness.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
<symbol name = "MANOTE" width = "5.132mm" height = "3.048mm"/>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
This symbol indicates that quarter-pillar outer panel and rear wheel house outer panel are replaced at the same time.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Vehicle left side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Vehicle right side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Applied part of body sealer.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
